This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with fine-grained visual recognition. It also involves machine learning techniques such as bilinear pooling, which suggests it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of multiple cross-layer bilinear features could also suggest a Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper involves recognition of visual data, which could also fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category.
